PART III. CORRECTIONS
SECTION 3.1. Section 2.3 of S.L. 2025-90 reads as rewritten:
"SECTION 2.3. David Longo of Mecklenburg County is appointed to the Metropolitan
Public Transportation Authority for a term of two four years to commence upon approval by the
Secretary of State of the articles of incorporation of the Metropolitan Public Transportation
Authority."
SECTION 3.2. Part II of S.L. 2025-1 reads as rewritten:
"…
"SECTION 2.5. Seth Ellington of Wake County is appointed to the Building Code Council
for a term expiring January 1, 2027.2029.
"SECTION 2.6. Paul Boney of New Hanover County is appointed to the Building Code
Council for a term expiring January 1, 2029.2031.
"SECTION 2.7. Mark Smith of Guilford County is appointed to the Building Code Council
for a term expiring January 1, 2031.2027."
PART IV. EFFECTIVE DATE
SECTION 4.1. This act is effective when it becomes law. Unless otherwise provided,
terms begin upon the effective date of this act.
In the General Assembly read three times and ratified this the 22nd day of June, 2026.
s/ Rachel Hunt
President of the Senate
s/ Howard Penny, Jr.
Presiding Officer of the House of Representatives
